    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for LawDog offers a clear hierarchy, anchored by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (84.25), who remains our most explosive play. Against Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** benefits from the highest base projection and a significant SP skill advantage, making him the centerpiece of our offensive strategy. Close behind in the \"Strong\" tier are **Lawrence Butler** (73.47) and **Will Smith** (71.86). **Lawrence Butler** is particularly intriguing as our lead-off candidate against Kodai Senga; his combination of high-order placement and dynamic platoon utility creates a high ceiling. **Will Smith** further bolsters our outlook, as favorable wind conditions and a solid matchup against Jack Leiter elevate his efficiency score well above the standard threshold.\n\nWe are hunting stolen bases and favorable park factors, which drives our confidence in **Bryson Stott** (69.44) and **Tyler Freeman** (69.05). Both benefit from playing against pitchers with slower deliveries, providing a meaningful bump for their SB upside. Furthermore, the trio of **Luis Arraez** (65.95), **Jung Hoo Lee** (61.43), and **Matt Chapman** (68.26) all see their scores climb significantly due to the venue\u2014playing in a hitter-friendly park against Chris Bassitt. While **Daulton Varsho** (54.72) sits at the edge of our starting requirements due to a tough matchup against Joe Ryan, he remains in the lineup to capitalize on his elite raw power.\n\nThe most difficult exclusion today was **Wenceel Perez** (52.66), who fell just shy of our rotation requirements. While he offers some utility against the matchup with Junk, his projected efficiency was dampened by a negative platoon adjustment that pushed him behind more stable starters like **Gavin Sheets** (57.17). Users should keep a close eye on the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Cal Raleigh**, **Will Smith**, **Gavin Sheets**, **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Lawrence Butler**, **Brendan Donovan**, 